args:
While the group makes camp for the night,
Ranzal struggles with whether or not he should
continue on with the prince. Suddenly, Volk
appears and encourages Ranzal to observe the
things happening in Grams before disappearing
as suddenly as he arrived.
There you are, Ranzal!\nI've been looking all over for ya.
Something wrong, man? You ain't been\nyourself since we hit North Grastaea.
...Luca. What're ya gonna do after this?
I'm gonna see things through with\n{player_name}, obviously.
Same here, of course. What I mean is,\nwhat're ya gonna do after that?
Are ya gonna keep travelin'\nwith the boss man forever?
Okay, do NOT tell me you're actually\nthinking of leaving us.
Keep yer smallclothes on, buddy.\nI ain't decided nothin' yet.
So you ARE thinking about it!
Think about yer dream for a second, Luca.\nYou wanna create a world where folks\nain't ever gotta fight, yeah?
Will, didja ever think about makin' that\nhappen on yer OWN, or is it only ever\ngonna happen if the prince leads the way?
Don't get me wrong. I ain't blamin' ya\nor tryin' to put the screws to ya here\nor anything like that.
I wanna keep travelin' with you and\nthe prince and everybody else. I do.
But right now, the boss has been robbed of\nhis sister and don't even know who he is\nno more. He's hurtin', and hurtin' bad.

I just wonder if it ain't kinda cruel for
all of us to shove our own hopes and
dreams on a guy what's carryin' all
that on his shoulders.
Could be my dream'll just end up\nbein' another burden for the guy.
Makes me wonder if I oughta work harder\nto make it happen myself, ya know?
Wow. I had no idea that was how you felt.
Weird thing to bring up outta the blue,\nI know. Anyway, think maybe I'm gonna\ngo cool my head a bit.
Heh. Look, I get that he's a big deal.\nLet's just hope he ain't also a big dummy.
I can see yer worth takin' a chance on.\nI'll show ya to the Mistholt.
(Helluva lot of time's passed\nsince that day.)
(But I can't just lean on the boss\nfor everything forever.)
(Might be I gotta strike out and start\nmakin' my own way in the world again.)
I see ya hidin' there, friend—now come\nout before I toss an axe or three at ya.
Heh heh heh. It's been a while, Ranzal.
Damn if you ain't the most persistent\ncockroach I ever met!
...Huh? Why're ya just standing there?\nAin't ya come here to fight?
Something is troubling you, friend,\nand there is no honor in besting a man\nin so weak a state as yours.
Happy to show ya how weak I am\nright here and now, pal.

I need no show of force to see that for
myself. You're as weak as the pathetic
false prince you follow—he who chose
his sister over his entire country.
You're headed to the city, yes?\nIn that case, you'll likely stumble across\nthem for yourself.
You mean Grams?\nStumble across what now?
The sins and crimes of the fortunate...\nThat place is rife with them, so I'm certain\nyou will find them.

Although you probably wouldn't be able to
find them even if you strained your eyes
hard enough to pop them from your skull!
Farewell, Ranzal! Aaaah ha ha ha!
Dammit! Why the hell would that freak\nshow up, spout nonsense, and take off?
Er, did something happen?\nYou look unsettled.
Ain't nothin', boss. Don't worry about it.
I see... But listen. I just wanted to say,\nI'm sorry to have dragged you all the way\nout here to North Grastaea.
That ain't no way to talk after all\nthe time we spent together.
Maybe not, but I certainly never would\nhave made it this far without you.\nI know that for an absolute fact.
So I'm going to give my all here in this\nnew land and prove myself worthy of all\nthe support you've given me.
We reach Grams tomorrow, so if you can't\nsleep, you might at least try to lie down\nand get a bit of rest.
Sorry for dropping in on you again.\nI'll see you tomorrow, Ranzal.
